page.title: 06SE Corner of_D_Block
page.content: The South East corner of the{D-block covers an area of the neighbouring town of{Falmouth,}the{Penryn Creek} flows into the sea, this area lies to the South.The stretch of land between {Penryn}and{Falmouth,}known as{ {Ponsharden},has a variety of small industrial and commercial buildings along the water front of the creek. Recently a large marina has been developed in the North-East corner of{ {79.30}and these are permanent berths for hundreds of boats. To the south of the creek the land rises to the highest point in{Falmouth.}This area is covered with residential buildings ,the majority of which is in the public building sector as council housing.
